  m_Name: Root Protection
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::Trailback.Demo.Features.Data.FeatureDemoData
  featureName: Root Protection
  shortDescription: Protect navigation categories from consuming their final history
    entry.
  fullDescription: 'Root Protection prevents Trailback from navigating beyond the
    final entry in a protected navigation category.


    When users return to the
    last available entry in a category and press Back again, Trailback doesn''t remove
    that entry or continue resolving history. Instead, it raises the `OnNavigationRootReached`
    event, allowing the application to decide what should happen next.


    Common
    use cases include:


    * Exit Confirmation Dialogs

    * Return To Main Menu

    *
    Application Exit Handling

    * Custom Navigation Workflows


    Benefits include:


    *
    Protected Navigation Roots

    * Predictable Navigation Boundaries

    * Safe
    History Resolution

    * Category-Level Root Protection

    * Configurable
    Root-Reached Events



    This makes it easy to define behavior for situations
    where users have reached the end of a navigation flow, while keeping navigation
    boundaries clear and predictable.


    The `OnNavigationRootReached` event can
    be handled through Inspector events, bridge events, or direct event subscriptions,
    depending on how Trailback is integrated into your project.'
  screenshots: []
  videoUrl: https://youtu.be/s7KsSg2JdM0
  documentationUrl: https://github.com/akpardeshi/Trailback/#navigation-root-reached
